.TH "rio_disc_peer" 9 "rio_disc_peer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rio_disc_peer \- Recursively discovers a RIO network through a master port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rio_disc_peer
.BI "(struct rio_net *net "  ","
.BI "struct rio_mport *port "  ","
.BI "u16 destid "  ","
.BI "u8 hopcount "  ","
.BI "struct rio_dev *prev "  ","
.BI "int prev_port "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "net" 12
RIO network being discovered
.IP "port" 12
Master port to send transactions
.IP "destid" 12
Current destination ID in network
.IP "hopcount" 12
Number of hops into the network
.IP "prev" 12
previous rio_dev
.IP "prev_port" 12
previous port number
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Recursively discovers a RIO network.  Transactions are sent via the
master port passed in \fIport\fP.
